    <briefdescription>
<para>Stores relational constraints and derives sign properties for simple patterns. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>When a relation of the form <computeroutput>variable op 0</computeroutput> is added, the <ref refid="de/db6/classlamina_1_1RelationStore" kindref="compound">RelationStore</ref> notifies the <ref refid="d3/dba/classlamina_1_1PropertyStore" kindref="compound">PropertyStore</ref> to mark the variable with the corresponding sign:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>GT → Positive</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>GEQ → NonNegative</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>LT → Negative</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>LEQ → NonPositive</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>NEQ → NonZero</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Composite relations (multi-variable LHS or non-zero RHS) are stored without decomposition for later use by the <ref refid="d2/d48/classlamina_1_1InferenceEngine" kindref="compound">InferenceEngine</ref>. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
